geo:siteIdentification.geo:notes: Monument was removed and the station decommissioned on 2016-03-04. The IGS site has been transferred to the SEY2 monument, which was built adjacent to SEY1 and has been running continuously since 2015-03-06.

geo:siteLocation.geo:notes: Site is collocated with the seismic station of UCSD on the lower pad of the former Air Force Tracking Station,10km NW of the International Airport at an altitute of 575m above sea level.

geo:CollocationInformation.geo:notes: UCSD operates a seismic station collocated with the GPS site.

geo:MultipathSource.geo:notes: 220 ft tower is guy wired into ground between recording room and seismic wellhead (antenna). Guy wires pass directly over GPS antenna. Site being used as vehicle turnaround, antenna cable is driven over each time. New Dormitory built 80-100 yards below site which houses 80-100 people.
